THE man who allegedly shot at the airborne police helicopter, injuring the pilot and assistant, was arrested on Wednesday, 23 February, in Tembisa, Ekurhuleni. This brings the number of arrested suspects in The Hill near Rosettenville to 11, following Monday’s bloody shooting. The suspect, aged 42, is expected to appear in the Tembisa Magistrates Court on Friday, 25 February, following his arrest during a crime intelligence-led multidisciplinary operation by the national CIT task team. The suspect was accosted in the street and a 9mm pistol found in his possession. ALSO READ: 10 CIT suspects killed in shoot-out! Hawks spokeswoman Brigadier Thandi Mbambo said in a statement: “Further investigation led to his place of residence, where a search was conducted. Four rifles, five pistols, including the one found in his possession, a rifle and pistol magazines, more than 1 000 ammunition, channel jammers, a G4S, SAPS bullet-proof vests and uniform were recovered.” The suspect has been charged with possession of unlicenced firearms, ammunition and suspected stolen property. Four police officers were injured in the shoot-out and one succumbed to his injuries on Tuesday. Police ministry spokeswoman Lirandzu Themba tweeted: “All SAPS members and a JMPD member, who were shot and injured during the ordeal, are recovering well.”